17. README Opening

You can use this nearly as-is.

README.md

# Preference Arena MVP
Preference Arena is a Pantheon-native reference implementation for turning pairwise choices into attributable value.
Users compare entities two at a time.
Those comparisons become binding records.
Binding records update preference models.
Preference models generate useful artifacts.
Useful artifacts generate credit back to contributors.
## Stack
- BLP: binding relationships
- CE: converting comparisons into structure
- CMP: packaging outputs into reusable value
- UICL: assigning trust and credit
## MVP domain
Pokémon preferences
## Future domains
Movies, fashion, collectibles, hiring, taste discovery, recommendation systems

